			<abstract>
				<p>Erich Nasch and Robert Weinberger, co-workers in the Documentation campaign, visited several former labor and concentration camps in Austria and Germany a few months after the war to gather evidence about the events of the Holocaust. In this particular report, they provide a short
					overview of the labor camp in Ebensee. Nasch and Weinberger not only focus on the events of the war, but they also discuss the present condition of the former Jewish prisoners staying at the camp. They describe their living conditions as unsatisfactory and express their worries
					about the Russians, who have an obvious tendency to speed up the repatriation of prisoners, even those who don't want to return to their homeland.</p>
			</abstract>
