		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="cs">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protokol č. 60</p>
					<p>Zpráva o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračním táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName>, <date when="1945-10-23">23. X. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Za <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Dokumentační akci</term> přijal: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">Scheck</persName></p>
					<p>Za archiv: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_tressler_harald">Tresssler</persName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Praha</placeName>, <date when="1946-01-29">29. I. 1946</date></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName>, dne <date when="1945-10-23">23. 10. 1945</date>.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Dokumentační akce</term></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName></p>
					<p>Zpráva o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračním</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">táboře</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName></p>
					<p>V nejkrásnější krajině <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakouska</placeName>, v Solné komoře, leží na jižním konci Traunského jezera <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-937" type="subject">průmyslové</term>
						městečko <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>. Několik set metrů od městečka leží na prudkém svahu řada <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barákových</term>
						komplexů s typickým vzhledem <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračního tábora</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">Tábor</term> byl založen v roce <date when="1942"
							>1942</date> a určen původně asi pro 2000 osob. Později však byly dopravovány do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> tisíce <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
							type="subject">vězňů</term> z evakuovaných <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táborů</term> z celého <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Německa</placeName>, takže průměrný stav
						byl kolem 20.000. Tím se stalo, že na pryčně 80 cm široké leželi 4, ba 5 lidí.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> nebyl <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">Vernichtungslager</term> v tom smyslu, že se tam lidé hromadně <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">popravili</term> nebo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">zaplynovali</term>, ale byli denně po stovkách <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">ubiti</term> při <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práci</term> nebo na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837"
							type="subject">bloku</term>. I jiné okolnosti spolupůsobily, že život se nedal vydržeti déle než 4 až 6 týdnů. 18.000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-904" type="subject">přeživších</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term> bylo vesměs jen úplně krátkou dobu tam, anebo měli tam nějaké lepší postavení. Ale i z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject"
							>osvobozených</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">skonalo</term> ještě asi 1500 následkem různých <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocí</term> a špatného zacházení v <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term>. Jsou <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-805" type="subject">pohřbeni</term> na důstojně upraveném <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">hřbitově</term> poblíž silnice mezi <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> a <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischlem</placeName>. Jsou tam řady červených dřevěných křížků, které se střídají s dřevěnými židovskými hvězdami.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Pracovalo</term> se skoro výhradně v podzemních <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">štolách</term>. Ve <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">skalách</term> byly vytvořeny chodby, některé přes kilometr dlouhé, které jsou mezi sebou spojeny a tvoří rozsáhlý systém podzemních chodeb a sálů. Vyrábělo a vyrábí se tam syntetický benzin, a
						měly tam býti umístěny i zbrojní <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">továrny</term> koncernu <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000153">Hermann-Göring</persName>-Werke, k čemuž však už nedošlo pro
						skončení <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">války</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Práce</term> byly vesměs velmi těžká. V <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">závodech</term> pro výrobu syntetického benzinu <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracují</term> toho času <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáci</term>, kteří <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">bydlí</term> v bývalém <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496"
							type="subject">koncentračním táboře</term>.</p>
					<p>Je to zajímavá podívaná, vidíme-li <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">tábor</term> střežený <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289">americkým vojskem</orgName>, <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289">amerického</orgName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">vojína</term> na strážní věži a <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">anglicko</placeName>-<placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">německý</placeName> nápis <q>electrified fence – elektrischer Zaun</q>. Viděli jsme ovšem také, že internovaní <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
							>esesáci</term> se při <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práci</term> nijak nepředřou, a slyšeli jsme, že smějí dostávat balíčky a že jejich <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
							>stravování</term> není horší než stravování židů, kteří jsou v blízkém <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term>, v bývalých <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
							>barácích</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáků</term>. V <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term> je malé <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501"
							type="subject">krematorium</term>, které v době velké <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-862" type="subject">úmrtnosti</term> nestačilo na spalování všech <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject"
							>mrtvol</term>, takže vedle něho je ještě <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">hromadný hrob</term> několika tisíců <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">zabitých</term>. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">Plynová komora</term> existovala prý v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term>, není však známo, že by byla v provozu.</p>
					<p>Peklem pro sebe byly tzv. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Schonungsblocky</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">Nemocní</term> tam leželi nazí na holé zemi, to málo <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">jídlo</term>, co měli dostat, jim bylo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">ukradeno</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-484" type="subject">blokovými</term>, takže dopravení na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Schonungsblock</term> se rovnalo rozsudku <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">smrti</term>.</p>
					<p>Z bývalých <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term> se nachází v blízkém <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term> /bývalých <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barácích</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>/ ještě 400 <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poláků</placeName>, z nich asi 200 židů. Jejich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">životní podmínky</term> nejsou uspokojivé. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Ubytování</term> by ušlo, stěžují si však na malé příděly <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potravin</term> a na to, že nikdo se nestará o jejich <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">ošacení</term>. Byly a jsou proto nuceni obstarávati si
						svoje životní potřeby adekvátní činností, t.j. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-933" type="subject">obchodováním</term>. Tím se dostávají stále do konfliktů s <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html"
							>rakouskými</placeName> a <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">americkými</placeName> úřady, čímž se jejich situace zase horší, což zase zvětšuje</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_03.png" n="3"/>
					<p>jejich nedostatek a tím pud k <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-933" type="subject">obchodování</term>.</p>
					<p>Stěžují si dále na nedostatečnou pomoc se strany <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-869" type="subject">židovských institucí</term>, ba poukazují dokonce na to, že jsou jimi <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660"
							type="subject">okrádány</term> a podváděny.</p>
					<p>S <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">arijskými</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poláky</placeName> v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term> žijí v napjatém poměru, co se nám v <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term> nejvíc líbilo, byla skoro vzorná pospolitost a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">bratrská</term> vzájemná pomoc mezi židovskými <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">muži</term> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">ženami</term>.</p>
					<p>Jízda <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">rakouským</placeName> územím ukazuje, že tato země byla poseta <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračními tábory</term>, a že sotva jedno místo
						nemá ve své blízkosti příšeru dvojitých ostnatých drátů. Situace bývalých <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term> v této zemi je oproti <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html"
							>Německu</placeName> horší tím, že <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakušané</placeName> jako <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-124" type="subject">občané</term> svobodného státu odmítají odpovědnost za
						nacistické zločiny a tím odpadají základy lepšího postavení <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňů</term> dané v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Německu</placeName>. V
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">ruském</placeName> pásmu nad to je zřetelná tendence provésti <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1226" type="subject">repatriaci</term>, a to co nejrychlejší, i těch osob,
						které se nechtějí vrátit do své vlasti.</p>
					<p>Část informací o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračním táboře</term> v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> nám poskytli bývalí <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">vězňové</term> tohoto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">tábora</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_bodenstein_moses">Bodenstein Moses</persName>, nar. <date when="1918">1918</date> v Koszici u <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakova</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_siegfried_benjamin">Siegfried Benjamin</persName>,
						nar. <date when="1908">1908</date> v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jaslo</placeName> a Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_bester_oskar">Bester Oskar</persName>, nar. <date when="1915">1915</date> ve <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vídni</placeName>, všichni t. č. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-278" type="subject">D.P. Camp</term> 3, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp"
							>Ebensee</placeName>.</p>
					<p>O <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">tábor</term> se stará místní expositury <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-001704">UNRRA</orgName>, mimo to je v <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-278" type="subject">D.P.</term> Committee, které nám dalo k dispozici <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">fotografie</term> a nějaký dokumentační materiál.</p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_nasch_erich">Nasch</persName></p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weinberger_robert">Weinberger</persName></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Statement no. 60</p>
					<p>Report on the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Concentration Camp</term></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName>, <date when="1945-10-23">23. X. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Accepted on behalf of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term>: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">Scheck</persName></p>
					<p>Accepted on behalf of the archive: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_tressler_harald">Tresssler</persName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <date when="1946-01-29">29. I. 1946</date></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName>, on <date when="1945-10-23">October 23rd, 1945</date></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184" type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName></p>
					<p>Report on the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Concentration Camp</term></p>
					<p>In the most beautiful <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName> countryside, in the salt cave, on the southern edge of Lake Traun, lies the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-937" type="subject"
							>industrial</term> small town of <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>. Several hundred meters from the town, on a steep slope, there are several <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">building</term> complexes with the typical architecture of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>. The <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was founded in <date when="1942">1942</date> and was originally designed to hold roughly 2,000 people. Later, however, thousands of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> from evacuated <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camps</term> from all over <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> were transported to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>, and so the average number of people here was around
						20,000. This meant that 4, even 5, people shared an 80 cm wide plank-bed.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> wasn’t a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">Vernichtungslager</term> in the sense that people weren’t <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">executed</term> or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">gassed</term> en masse here, but were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">beaten to death</term> by the hundreds every day while they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> or were on the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">block</term>. Combined with other circumstances, the toil here could not be endured for more than 4 to 6 weeks. The 18,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-904"
							type="subject">surviving</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> were either only here for a very short time, or had a better position within the camp system. But roughly 1,500 of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> from various <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">diseases</term> and as a result of their bad treatment in the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. They were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-805" type="subject">buried</term> in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747"
							type="subject">cemetery</term> that was renovated with dignity near the road between <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-184"
							type="camp">Bad Ischl</placeName>. In it, there are rows of red crosses, which alternate with wooden Jewish stars.</p>
					<p>We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> almost the whole time in underground <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">tunnels</term>. Paths were created within the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">cliffs</term>, some over a kilometer in length, that were interconnected and made up an enormous system of underground tunnels and rooms. We manufactured synthetic gasoline, which is still
						manufactured here today, and a weapons <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">plant</term> of the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000153">Hermann-Göring</persName>-Werke was supposed to be located
						here, but this never happened because of the end of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> was extremely difficult.
						Today, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS men</term> who <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">live</term> in the former <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camp</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in the synthetic gasoline <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term>.</p>
					<p>It is a strange sight to see the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> guarded by <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289">American troops</orgName>, an <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289">American</orgName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> on the guard tower, and the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">English</placeName>-<placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName> sign <q>electrified fence – elektrischer Zaun.</q> But we also see that the interned <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSmen</term>
						don’t <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> too hard, and hear that they are allowed to receive packages, and that their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> isn’t
						worse than the food for the Jews in the nearby <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, in the former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>. There was a small <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematorium</term> in the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, and during a period of high <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-862" type="subject">mortality</term> it couldn’t keep up with the burning of all of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">dead bodies</term>, and so there was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">mass grave</term> of several thousand <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">murdered</term> people next to it. There was apparently a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas chamber</term> in the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, but we never found out if it was ever used.</p>
					<p>The so-called <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Schonungsblocks</term> were a special sort of hell. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> lay there naked on the bare
						ground, what little <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> they were to get was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">stolen</term> by <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-484" type="subject">block leaders</term>, and therefore being sent to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">Schonungsblock</term> was like a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> sentence.</p>
					<p>Besides the former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term>, 400 <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poles</placeName>, about 200 of which are Jews, are housed in the nearby <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> (the former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>). Their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">living conditions</term> are not satisfactory. Their <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">accommodations</term> are adequate, but they complain about their small <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> rations and that nobody cares
						about their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term>. They are therefore forced to procure necessities by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-933" type="subject">trading</term>. This angers the
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">American</placeName> authorities, which makes their situation worse, and that only increases</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-011_03.png" n="3"/>
					<p>their poverty, and thus they have to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-933" type="subject">trade</term>.</p>
					<p>They also complain about not getting enough help from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-869" type="subject">Jewish institutions</term>, and have stated that they have even been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660"
							type="subject">robbed</term> and cheated by them.</p>
					<p>They live alongside the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poles</placeName> in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> in a tense atmosphere. What we enjoyed most in the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was the practically exemplary solidarity and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brotherly</term> mutual help between Jewish <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>.</p>
					<p>A trip trough <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> reveals that this country was full of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>, and there is barely a
						town without a monstrous double barbed wire fence nearby. The situation of the former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> in this country is worse than in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> because the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrians</placeName>, as <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-124"
							type="subject">citizens</term> of a free country, have refused to take responsibility for Nazi crimes and so the elevated position of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoners</term> in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> is not the same here. In the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName> sector there is an obvious tendency to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1226" type="subject">repatriate</term> as fast as possible, even people who don’t want to return to their home country.</p>
					<p>Some of the information about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camp</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName> was provided to us by the
						former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">inmates</term> of this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_bodenstein_moses">Bodenstein Moses</persName>, born in <date when="1918">1918</date> in Koszici near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakow</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_siegfried_benjamin">Siegfried
							Benjamin</persName>, born in <date when="1908">1908</date> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jaslo</placeName>, and Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_bester_oskar">Bester Oskar</persName>, born in <date when="1915">1915</date> in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName>, and all of those currently in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-278" type="subject">D. P.</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-278" type="subject">Camp</term> 3, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>.</p>
					<p>The local branch of <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-001704">UNRRA</orgName> is overseeing the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, and the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-278" type="subject">D.P.</term> Committee is also in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-573" type="camp">Ebensee</placeName>, which provided us with <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photographs</term> and some documentary material.</p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_nasch_erich">Nasch</persName></p>
					<p>Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weinberger_robert">Weinberger</persName></p>
				</div>
			</div>
